history.content:
I am taking 61B with Prof. Hilfinger this semester.
Homework and labs are easy, about 2-3h per week, I didn't really count.
The first project was easy and similar to 61A projects, took me less than 10h, but the second one is much harder, I spent 30+h on it, including testing and passing AG tests.
Exams are pretty straight forward, they do not mean to trick you like 61A. Spent about 10 hours doing all the Hilfinger's past exams for MT1.

children.subject: Haha no I meant 20 hour TA position, sorry for the confusion

If you're employed by the university as an ASE, you should not be regularly putting in more hours than you are employed for. If this occurs, you should speak with your supervisor to decrease the workload, or speak with the student union if that doesn't work.

This being said, TA positions generally have some surges and lulls of time commitment depending on what part of the course they control. For example: the 20-hour TA in my course is uninvolved with midterms and has almost complete management over projects. Thus their workload is highest in the weeks leading up to each project release and somewhat lower in the space between project releases.

history.content: Can anyone comment on this? How hard is it, and what would you say is the real weekly hour commitment, whether it be more or less?
